  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is it good to have Milk during fever?",
  "response": "When you're dealing with a fever, dietary choices can play a role in how comfortable you feel and how quickly you recover. Milk is generally considered safe and can even be beneficial when you have a fever, provided you don't have any allergies or intolerances. Here are a few points to consider:\n\n1. **Nutritional Value**: Milk is a good source of essential nutrients such as calcium, vitamin D, protein, and calories, which can be helpful if you're not eating much as a result of your illness.\n\n2. **Hydration**: Staying hydrated is crucial when you have a fever because fever can lead to increased fluid loss. While milk can contribute to your fluid intake, it's important to also drink water and other clear fluids.\n\n3. **Mucus Production**: Some people find that dairy products can thicken mucus, although scientific evidence on this is mixed. If you have a cough or a lot of mucus production, you might want to observe whether milk seems to exacerbate these symptoms for you.\n\n4. **Digestive Comfort**: During a fever, your digestive system might be more sensitive, and some people find milk to be heavy or hard to digest. If this is the case, opt for lighter foods.\n\n5. **Lactose Intolerance**: If you're lactose intolerant, consuming milk can lead to digestive discomfort, which is something you would want to avoid when already dealing with a fever.\n\nOverall, if you enjoy milk and are not sensitive to it, you can include it in your diet during a fever. Just be mindful of how your body responds and ensure you're also consuming a balanced diet with plenty of fluids. If you're unsure or have specific health concerns, it's always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional.",
